            },
            "answer_text": "Identical twins will have the same eye color. There are a few genes involved in eye color, and their genes are identical. It is possible for environmental factors after birth (epigenomics) to cause differences in the expression of genes, and therefore giving each twin a different phenotype (or trait). To my knowledge, eye color is not heavily influenced by the environment, so you\u2019re not going to observe drastic difference like one brown-eyed and one blue-eyed identical twins. My twin sister and I have blue eyes, but more specifically dark blue eyes with a yellow hue. It\u2019s unique to our family line. My two daughters have blue eyes, but without the yellow hue. ",
