            "answer_text": "Genetically identical twins can have different eye colors because DNA sequences don\u2019t determine traits. Modern science has revealed epigenetic mechanisms that regulate characteristics of organisms. Eye and pigment color is mostly affected by melanin production associated genes, such as OCA2, HERC2 and SLC45A. Every one of these genes are alternatively spliced. Splice variants are regulated by epigenetic factors, such as CpG methylation and histone markers. ",
