            "answer_text": "Except for some odd mishap, identical twins will have the same eye color. Identical twins have the exact same DNA. They are the result of one sperm fertilizing one egg. At a very early stage, the newly growing individual splits apart into two separate pieces. Each of these two pieces then continues to develop into a separate child. They are genetically identical because they have the exact same DNA. Identical twins cannot have two separate fathers as it is impossible for one sperm to come from two separate men. ",
